Hyprland allows for multiple types of layouts

# Dwindle Layout

This layout keeps halving the window size of the active window to spawn the new window.

The Dwindle Layout is good for monitors that don't have a lot of windows, like vertical monitors.

# Master Layout

This layout allows for a large master window and then tiles the other windows around it.

To create a stable master layout with the master window in the center that stays "shrunk" even with no other windows available (useful for ultrawide displays like 32:9), you can use the following in your .config:

```
master {
  orientation = center
  always_keep_position = true
  slave_count_for_center_master = 0
}
```
